  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0ba8\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bae\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1 \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bb3\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc8 \u0baa\u0bca\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0bb8\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc0\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc0\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bae\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bcb\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0ba4\u0bc1.\u0bb0\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb0\u0ba9\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "If the police violate the court order, we will go to court again - Dr. Ravikaran",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "If the police are violating the court order, then we intend to go to the court again,\" said Durairasa Ravikaran, a former North Provincial Assembly member.",
        "He said this when contacted and inquired about the Mullaitivu Kuzumuna Kurundur Hill issue.",
        "Tamil heritage and the very ancient Adhisiva Iyanar Temple is a place of worship by Saivite Tamils \u200b\u200bsince time immemorial. As per the order of the case filed on 06.09.2018 regarding Kurundur Hill, it includes many orders along with the order not to build new constructions.",
        "But on 12.06.2022, efforts were made to carry out massive Buddhist imposing activities in the said temple with the aim of erecting a Buddha statue on a very large scale. On that day, the efforts to impose Buddhism were stopped due to the massive opposition of the people and the representatives of the people.",
        "Again, on 16.06.2022 i.e. four days after their attempts were made on 12.06.2022, I, Sasikumar and Sriskandarasa, the villagers of Kumhomunai, filed a case through a moving deed.",
        "That is, we have filed this motion against the order of the case dated 06.09.2018.",
        "The Mullaitivu lawyers argued the respective installments in a very good manner. That is, two installments were made on 23.06.2022 and one installment on 30.06.2022 and the hearings were held and on 14.07.2022 Mullaitivu District Magistrate Court Judge R. Saravanaraja issued the following orders.",
        "After hearing the arguments of both sides, the judge ordered that all the constructions, including temples, statues, and shrines erected in Kurundur hill region, should be removed and the police should submit a report to the court after removing the constructions.",
        "Next, he issued an order that no one should obstruct the traditional Kurundurmalai Adhisivan Ayyanar Pooja worship events in any way. Next, as the said area is under the jurisdiction of the Department of Archaeology, a notification was issued to submit the related research reports to the Department of Archaeology.",
        "Subsequently, it was informed that the police should provide their security so that there is no disturbance of peace at the place mentioned in the order. These are the views expressed by Mullaitivu District Court Judge.",
        "Next we expect the situation where the police will have to take these steps and we have an idea that after a certain period of time we will go to the court again. Because if they don't take any action, if the police are violating the court orders, then of course we intend to go to the court again,\" he added."
      ],
